(2618, 863, 'long_description', '  <p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Real Madrid took a big leap towards the Semi-Finals with a 1-0 win at Leganes in the 1st Leg last week. They took a risk by leaving a host of key players out but a late Marco Asensio goal leaves Leganes with a massive task on their hands in this week’s return clash at the Bernabeu.</span></p>\r\n               <p><span style="font-weight: 400;">They should at least be able to make a pretty good game of it. Leganes once again showed what an organised and well disciplined side they are in that first game, which was a pretty even contest. They certainly will not capitulate in the same way that Deportivo La Coruna did at the Bernabeu at the weekend. </span></p>\r\n               <p><span style="font-weight: 400;">The minnows from the South of the capital have only suffered two defeats all season by a margin of greater than one goal. Defensively they’ve been very impressive, conceding just one goal per game on average in La Liga, a record only three teams can better. With a 9 point advantage on the relegation zone, they aren’t in a position of immediate danger so they can afford to give this a good go and we’re likely to see another strong team from them.</span></p>\r\n               <p><span style="font-weight: 400;">WIth Real Madrid having only won one of their last four home games in all competitions and having already suffered three home league defeats this term, they will sense they are vulnerable right now. Their home showings in the Copa del Rey have been less than convincing too. So far this season at home in the cup, Real Madrid have picked up two 2-2 draws, both against lower league opponents.</span></p>\r\n               <p><span style="font-weight: 400;">With a really tough trip to Valencia to come this weekend in La Liga, just three days after this match, Zinedine Zidane is highly likely to stick with his policy of rotating heavily in this competition. Few of his fringe players have really stuck their hand up though and done enough to suggest they warrant a more regular run in the side and the team that does line up for this game is unlikely to have enough about them to run riot against a strong Leganes defence.</span></p>\r\n               <p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Overall backing Leganes +2.0 Asian Handicap looks to offer value as the minnows look to make history by recording their first win at the Bernabeu. <a href="http://www.freesupertips.co.uk/asian-handicap-betting-guide/">Read more about Asian Handicap betting here</a>.</span></p>\r\n               <p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Los Blancos should still have enough to edge it though. However with just one clean sheet in their last 6 Copa del Rey home games, the visitors could nick a goal and going for 2-1 Real Madrid looks a decent bet in the correct score market.</span></p>\r\n               <div class="more">\r\n                  <p>If you want to win big today then follow our <a href="/accumulator-tips/">Football accumulator tips</a>!</p>\r\n               </div>'),
