(150, 1, '2017-12-06 05:49:16', '2017-12-06 05:49:16', '<div class="fst segment blog content" id="seocontent"><h1>Free Boxing Betting Tips</h1><p>Unsure of who to back for the next big boxing bout?</p><p>Here at Free Super Tips our expert tipsters put the research in so you don’t have to, providing you with regular boxing predictions to keep you going all year round. Whether you’re watching the next heayweight title defence, one of the many undercards to the big bouts, or some of the lesser known regular fights we have boxing betting tips for you!</p><p>As with all of our sports betting tips, this is all completely free! There are no subscriptions to pay or extortionate sign-up fees. Just the very best boxing betting tips.</p><h2>When Are Your Boxing Tips Posted?</h2><p>Boxing betting is a little different to most other sports due to their lack of a recognised season, but with regular bouts taking place among the WBO, WBA, WBC, and IBC organisations as well as amateur boxing matches and regional events this simply means we can provide boxing predictions throughout the year.</p><p>Understandably most fights take place over the weekend, and we aim to update our boxing betting tips page with the latest boxing predictions by the Thursday to give you plenty of time to back our boxing tips before the action starts.</p><h2>Predictions for Boxing Title Fights</h2><p>With so many different weight classes and organisations in the sport, boxing generally sees at least one major title fight every month of the year. Naturally some of these are more hotly anticipated than others, and for these marquee bouts we offer a range of boxing predictions to cover a number of different markets.</p><p>Whether you are a fair-weather fan who only tunes in for the next Anthony Joshua bout or if you follow every weight division and watch every weekend, we have all the boxing betting tips you will ever need!</p><h3>Boxing Predictions for Major Upcoming Events</h3><h3>Floyd Mayweather and Conor McGregor: 26th August in Las Vegas</h3><p>The most audacious fight in boxing has been set. Floyd Mayweather confirmed that the matchup between himself and UFC star Conor McGregor will take place from the T-Mobile Arena in Las Vegas on August 26th.&nbsp;It will take place at 154lbs, the boxing light middleweight division and a pound beneath the UFC lightweight division that McGregor rules. Both fighters are set to take home a stupendous purse with the total revenue expected to exceed any other previous boxing match in pay per view history.</p><h2>Predictions for Undercard Fights</h2><p>Each major boxing event is preceded by one or more undercard fights in boxing so as to provide some additional entertainment for viewers. These generally involve some of the lesser known or up and coming boxing stars, and as such with some thorough research it’s possible to extract a lot of value from the bookmakers. Our tipsters do just that to give you free boxing tips for all the major undercard bouts.</p><h2>Weekly Boxing Tips</h2><p>Whilst there may not be a headline bout every weekend, with so many organisations, regional titles, and amateur boxing as well there are opportunities for boxing betting every single weekend. Our expert tipsters scour the upcoming fights and root out the very best value for our boxing predictions, so you don’t have to wait until the title fights to make money from our boxing tips.</p><h2>The Best Boxing Betting Odds</h2><p>Providing you with excellent boxing predictions isn’t enough for our determined tipsters! They also go above and beyond to root out the best possible odds for each of their boxing tips in order to save you time and money. All you need to do is visit our boxing betting page and our predictions will point you towards the best value odds on the market.</p><p>In addition to this, you can also head over to our <a href="http://stagingonline.net/projects/freesupertips/free-bets/">Boxing Free Bets</a> page where new and existing members can extract even more value from our boxing tips with an array of exclusive offers from our betting partners.</p><h2>Follow Us on Twitter</h2><p>For live updates on our boxing tips and a range of other sports betting opportunities – along with all the latest sporting news and humour – follow us at <a href="https://twitter.com/FootySuperTips">@FootySuperTips.</a></p></div>', 'Boxing Tips', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'boxing-tips', '', '', '2018-01-16 06:42:22', '2018-01-16 06:42:22', '', 0, 'http://localhost/sirtips/?page_id=150', 0, 'page', '', 0),
(151, 1, '2017-12-06 05:49:37', '2017-12-06 05:49:37', '<div class="ui horizontal divider invis_clss" style="margin-top:1em;"><i class="ui white custom info icon"></i> More Info</div>\r\n<div class="fst segment blog content" id="seocontent"><h1>Free Cricket Betting Tips</h1><p>If you’re after free cricket betting tips, you have come to the right place! Our expert cricket tipsters here at Free Super Tips will provide you with cricket betting tips for all of the international tournaments and major fixtures. Whether you’re after tips&nbsp;for the Cricket World Cup, Indian Premier League or T20, we’ve got you covered with our cricket predictions and of course, all of our tips are free and always will be.</p><h2>When Are Your Cricket Tips Posted?</h2><p>The times our cricket tips are posted at vary depending on the fixture list but we like to give our followers as much time as possible to read our tips and be able to get on the bets so we will usually post tournament previews up to a week in advance.</p><p>Make sure you bookmark this page and check back regularly for your free cricket tips all year round.</p><h2>What Cricket Predictions Do You Do?</h2><p>We like to cover as much of the cricket season as possible especially the major tournaments below that are so good to bet on.</p><h2>Cricket World Cup</h2><p>The biggest tournament in the cricket calendar. The ICC Cricket World Cup is held every four years in a limited overs contest involving all test and ODI playing nations. It is one of the largest and most viewed sporting events in the world so make sure you’re following us for all of your Cricket World Cup betting tips.</p><h2>Indian Premier League</h2><p>The Indian Premier League is the most attended cricket league in the world and is enjoyed by millions of cricket fans during April and May each yeah. We will be offering you free IPL betting tips before the tournament as well as free IPL match predictions for every game during the tournament.</p><h2>World Twenty20</h2><p>Every two years, 16 teams battle it out in the T20 World Cup. ICC World Twenty20 is one of our favourite tournaments to cover so check back on gameday for our free cricket betting tips and predictions.</p><h2>The Ashes</h2><p>A longtime rivalry sees England and Australia battle it out for one of the smallest trophies in sport, the Ashes urn. This special test series occurs roughly every two years with five test matches each lasting up to five days. As always, our tips for the Ashes will be free for you.</p><h2>Get Notifications Of Our Cricket Tips</h2><p>For live updates on our cricket tips as well as the rest of the sports betting tips we cover, make sure you are following us on Twitter <a href="https://twitter.com/FootySuperTips">@FootySuperTips&nbsp;</a>&nbsp;where you will be notified of when all of our tips are posted.</p></div>', 'Cricket Tips', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'cricket-tips', '', '', '2018-01-16 06:43:27', '2018-01-16 06:43:27', '', 0, 'http://localhost/sirtips/?page_id=151', 0, 'page', '', 0),
(152, 1, '2017-12-06 05:49:51', '2017-12-06 05:49:51', '<div class="ui horizontal divider invis_clss" style="margin-top:1em;"><i class="ui white custom info icon"></i> More Info</div>\r\n<div class="fst segment blog content" id="seocontent"><h1>Free Darts Betting Tips</h1><p>Here at Free Super Tips our expert tipsters offer free betting tips on a wide range of sports, and the growing popularity of darts betting hasn’t evaded us. If you’re wondering who to back at the next darts tournament, look no further than our expertly selected free darts predictions.</p><p>Whether you’re watching the PDC World Darts Championship, the Betway Premier League Darts, or one of the many unranked tournaments – we have darts tips for you. Our tipsters thoroughly research each tournament and dig out the best value for our darts tips. Not only this but we also ensure you get the best odds available by scouting out the best price for our darts predictions.</p><p>We aren’t called Free Super Tips for nothing – There are absolutely no subscriptions, sign-up fees, or memberships to worry about. We simply provide you with the very best darts predictions for all the big matches!</p><h2>When Are Your Darts Tips Posted?</h2><p>The times for our darts predictions for the major tournaments varies depending on the fixture list, but for the Darts Premier League we update our darts betting tips page on the Tuesday in preparation for the fixtures to be played on Thursday. Overall major tournament predictions will be posted in the days leading up to the start of the event to give you plenty of time to back our darts tips before the tournament gets underway. Make sure to check back on our darts betting tips page every week for all the latest predictions.</p><h2>Predictions for the Betway Premier League Darts</h2><p>Beginning on the 2<sup>nd</sup> of February the Betway Premier League Darts runs until the middle of May, and our tipsters provide their thoroughly researched darts predictions for the main fixtures of every week to ensure you get regular darts betting action. As noted above, the darts tips will be updated on Tuesday in time for the fixtures on Thursday.</p><p>Michael van Gerwen is the defending champion for 2017, and with 15 weekly rounds of matches followed by the play-offs there will be plenty of chance to profit from our darts tips.</p><h2>Predictions for All Major Darts Tournaments</h2><h3>PDC World Darts Championship</h3><p>The PDC World Darts Championship is the biggest tournament of the PDC schedule and is held at the Circus Tavern in Purfleet between late December and early January. It’s the first taste of darts betting action of the new year, and with such a huge prize pool and the world’s best players it makes for fantastic viewing. It’s the biggest of all the PDC tournaments, so you can be sure there will be plenty of darts tips.</p><h3>Coral UK Open</h3><p>‘The FA Cup of darts’ changed schedule back in 2014 and is now played in March every year at Butlin’s Minehead. With unseeded draws and a wide variety of skill levels in this tournament the potential for upset is rife for even the top players, making this one of the most entertaining tournaments around. It also offers some excellent value for our darts predictions.</p><h3>BetVictor World Matchplay</h3><p>Held every July at the Winter Gardens in Blackpool this is regarded as the second biggest tournament after the PDC World Darts Championship. It is based around a legs format, allowing us extra markets to utilise in our darts betting tips.</p><h3>PartyPoker World Grand Prix</h3><p>Held in Dublin at the Citywest Hotel every October the PartyPoker World Grand Prix adds an unusual twist to televised darts tournaments by requiring players to finish each leg on a double, including the bullseye. This can lead to some unexpected outcomes, and as such our tipsters look to dig out that extra value for our darts betting tips.</p><h3>Singha Beer Grand Slam of Darts</h3><p>The Grand Slam of Darts has taken place every November at the Wolverhampton Civic since it’s inception in 2007. It’s the only UK based tournament to feature players from both the PDC and the BDO, which can result in some interesting matches for our darts predictions to focus on.</p><h3>Players Championship Finals</h3><p>Our favourite darts players revisit Butlin’s in Minehead in November as they compete for the Players Championship Finals, with the top 64 players competing to win part of the £400,000 prize fund. As always, our darts betting tips will guide you through the tournament.</p><h3>Partypoker European Championship</h3><p>Taking place in a variety of locations and months since it’s inception in 2008, the PartyPoker European Championship invites the top 32 European darts players to compete for the title of Europe’s best. This year it takes place in Hasselt, Belgium at the end of October, and our tipsters will be on hand with all the darts betting tips you can ask for.</p><h3>Everything Else</h3><p>The Premier League Darts and PDC major tournaments make up the bulk of our darts betting tips, but it doesn’t end there. With the BDO also hosting a number of major tournaments and countless minor tournaments throughout the season you can expect expert darts predictions throughout the entire year! We would suggest checking our darts betting tips page and our <a href="https://twitter.com/FootySuperTips">Twitter account</a> on a regular basis to ensure you don’t miss out on our darts predictions.</p><h2>The Best Darts Betting Odds</h2><p>Our tipsters don’t stop at providing you with excellent darts predictions. They also go above and beyond to find the absolute best odds for each of the darts tips they post, Saving you the hassle of trawling through countless bookmakers to find the best odds for our darts tips. Instead you can simply visit our Darts betting page and find the best bets and the best odds all in one easy to find location.</p><p>You can even head over to our <a href="http://stagingonline.net/projects/freesupertips/free-bets/">Darts free bets</a> page where both new and current members can further increase their value with an array of exclusive offers from our betting partners.</p><h2>Follow Us on Twitter</h2><p>For live updates on our darts tips and a range of other sports betting opportunities – along with all the latest sporting news and humour – follow us at <a href="https://twitter.com/FootySuperTips">@FootySuperTips.</a></p></div>', 'Darts Tips', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'darts-tips', '', '', '2018-01-16 06:43:50', '2018-01-16 06:43:50', '', 0, 'http://localhost/sirtips/?page_id=152', 0, 'page', '', 0),
