 are new to betting on&nbsp;the NHL.</p><h2>NHL Betting Terms Explained</h2><ul><li><strong>Money Line –&nbsp;</strong>this is a term used in all American sports which means ‘To&nbsp;Win’. If you are backing a team on the money line then they must win for your bet to be correct E.g. Chicago Blackhawks&nbsp;Money Line = Chicago Blackhawks&nbsp;to Win.</li><li><strong>Puck&nbsp;Line –&nbsp; </strong>the run line&nbsp;works the same as handicaps in football betting&nbsp;E.g. LA Kings -1.5 @ Boston Bruins+1.5. So with this 1.5 run line, the Boston Bruins&nbsp;must win the game outright or lose by 1.5 runs&nbsp;or less (two or less in reality) to cover the spread and for your bet to win. If the LA Kings&nbsp;win, they must do so by 1.5 runs or more (two or more in reality) for your bet to win. If the spread is set at a whole number E.g. LA Kings&nbsp;-1 @ Boston Bruins+1 and your team wins/loses by that exact number of runs&nbsp;then your bet is considered a push and your stake will be refunded.</li><li><b>Alternative Puck Line&nbsp;–&nbsp;</b>&nbsp;the same as above but we alter the standard run line to a different number of runs. These are essential for backing our daily banker doubles where we use the line a lot.</li><li><strong>Game Totals&nbsp;–&nbsp;</strong>the total number of goals&nbsp;scored in the game by both sides. This bet works just like Football<strong>.&nbsp;</strong>E.g. LA Kings @ Boston Bruins&nbsp;– Over/Under 5.5 goals&nbsp;means we need 6 goals&nbsp;or more to win the Overs and 5 goals or less to win the Unders. As with the puck line, if the game total&nbsp;is a whole number E.g. 5&nbsp;and the total goals&nbsp;scored are 5, then your bet becomes a push and your stake is refunded.</li><li><strong>Alternative Game Totals –&nbsp;</strong>&nbsp;the same as the previous but just a different number of goals. Found under the ‘main props’ tab then&nbsp;alternative totals.</li><li><b>Parlay –&nbsp;</b>a parlay is a term the American’s use for accumulators.