ive wins against Huddersfield and Southampton, and whilst finishing 2nd in their Champions League group will still sting them, they are carrying a bit of good form into the Christmas period now.\r\n\r\nAntonio Conte looks to have tried to bolster his defence in recent weeks too, as their 1-0 win against Southampton at the weekend illustrates. They built their title winning campaign on their solid back line, but it’s faltered far too many times this season and it looks like Conte has finally addressed the situation now.\r\n\r\nThis is especially true on home soil, where they have kept a clean sheet in three of their last five matches in all competitions and won four of them. There are expected to be some changes to the lineup for this match though, at least if their last round fixture against Everton is anything to go by.\r\n\r\nWilly Caballero could start between the sticks with Antonio Rudiger returning, but other than that their defensive setup could remain untouched. Besides that we could see Kenedy, Ampadu, Musonda, and Batshuayi brought in, but none of them should have an impact in the defensive aspect.\r\n\r\nBournemouth, on the other hand, are likely to be playing a full strength squad as they hunt for some unlikely silverware this season. Eddie Howe could opt for some changes though, especially after seeing his side hammered 4-0 at home to Liverpool on Sunday.\r\n\r\nThe Cherries are now winless in six matches in all competitions and find themselves struggling a bit, although away from home they tend to be a little tighter at the back. They only conceded one at Manchester United last week and limited Spurs to one as well. Their lack of scoring ability is an issue though, and it has resulted in four of their last six away games seeing fewer than three goals.\r\n\r\nChelsea have only seen one of their last five at home end with three or more goals as well, but despite this the bookies are expecting a goalfest. This leaves value out there for us, and backing Under 2.5 Goals at this price is fantastic value, along with a tight 1-0 win for the hosts.\r\n<div class="more">\r\n\r\n<a href="/free-football-betting-tips/">Football predictions</a> including accumulators, both teams to score, both teams to score and win, correct score and £10 to £1,000 challenge!\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<h2 class="preview-dark-heading">Head To Head</h2>\r\n<div class="text-content">\r\n\r\nChelsea have won four and lost one of their five previous meetings with Bournemouth.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<h2 class="preview-dark-heading">Chelsea vs Bournemouth Stats</h2>\r\n<div class="text-content">\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>80% of Chelsea’s last five competitive home games have seen fewer than three goals.</li>\r\n 	<li>The Blues have kept a clean sheet in 67% of these matches as well, winning 50% of them 1-0.</li>\r\n 	<li>Bournemouth have seen fewer than three goals in 67% of their last six away matches, losing 33% of them 1-0.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<h2 class="preview-dark-heading">Chelsea Team News</h2>\r\n<div class="text-content">\r\n<div class="team-news">\r\n\r\n<img class="team-news-badge" src="http://www.freesupertips.co.uk/wp-content/themes/freesupertips/image/team/Chelsea.png" alt="" />\r\n\r\nDavid Luiz is the only confirmed absentee for Chelsea.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<h2 class="preview-dark-heading">Bournemouth Team News</h2>\r\n<div class="text-content">\r\n<div class="team-news">\r\n\r\n<img class="team-news-badge" src="http://www.freesupertips.co.uk/wp-content/themes/freesupertips/image/team/Bournemouth.png" alt="" />\r\n\r\nBrad Smith and Tyrone Mings remain sidelined for The Cherries.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<h2 class="preview-dark-heading">Chelsea vs Bournemouth Predictions</h2>\r\n<div class="pg_container">\r\n<div class="pg_grid_container">\r\n<div class="pg_previewBet-row">\r\n<div class="pg_previewBet-betName">\r\n<div>Under 2.5 Match Goals at 11/8</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="pg_previewBet-betBtnContainer">\r\n<div class="pg_pre