(585, 1, '2017-12-22 17:47:52', '2017-12-22 17:47:52', 'Troyes may not be in the best form, though their Saturday night victory over Lyon will have helped matters, but they have a big opportunity to progress in this competition, as they face a St Etienne side who’ve been easy to beat of late. The hosts will be feeling good after their win at the weekend, while they’ll also be able to draw upon the positive experience of beating this opposition in the league back in October.</p>\r\nSt. Etienne are a team who’re struggling in Ligue 1 this season; Jean-Louis Gasset’s men find themselves hovering dangerously close to the relegation zone. Considering they’re a side who like to be challenging for the Europa League places, such form just won’t do. With this in mind, it’s reasonable to assume that progression in the Coupe de France may not be their main priority, as avoiding the drop and pushing themselves up the table is likely to be far higher on their list of priorities.\r\n\r\nTroyes are also a side who’re not far above the drop-zone, in fact they’re just one point above St. Etienne, though the fact that this match comes on home soil, where they’ve often performed very well, gives them that little bit more freedom.\r\n\r\nAt the prices, it’s impossible to oppose the hosts. Quite frankly, it’s remarkable that they’re not considered favourites in the pre-match betting. Backing Jean-Louis Garcia’s side to win back-to-back home games is very much the way to go.\r\n\r\nWhen playing at home, Troyes have been at their best this season. Wednesday’s hosts come into this match after a pleasing win (and performance) against Lille at the weekend, while they’ve generally been very tough to beat on their own patch during the current campaign. Scoring goals has tended to be the main issue, but they’ve rarely struggled in that department against the weaker sides. What’s more, a shocking St. Etienne back-line, one that has conceded an average of almost two goals per game on the road, should help them to be productive in the final third.\r\n\r\nRecent home wins against the likes of Lille, Amiens, Angers and Strasbourg bode well for the hosts, while their victory over St. Etienne at this venue in the league will also fill them with confidence.\r\n\r\nIn contrast, St. Etienne’s performances on the road have been anything but uplifting. Wednesday’s visitors have struggled massively at both ends of the pitch when playing away from the comforts of home. Six away defeats on the bounce, whereby St. Etienne have conceded a worrying total of 15 goals and scored just two, precede this match. Gasset’s men have offered very little in terms of forward creativity over the last few months, while they’ve been all too easy to breach at the other end. As a result, it’s very hard to fancy them ahead of this match, especially at the odd-looking prices.\r\n', 'Fleetwood Town vs Gillingham', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'fleetwood-town-vs-gillingham', '', '', '2018-01-25 06:29:50', '2018-01-25 06:29:50', '', 0, 'http://localhost/sirtips/?post_type=matches&#038;p=585', 0, 'matches', '', 0),
