(698, 1, '2018-01-04 13:42:24', '2018-01-04 13:42:24', '<!-- white box -->\r\n<h2>What is a win accumulator?</h2>\r\nA win accumulator is a very simple bet, we simply pick teams we think are going to win the match and put them all in a football accumulator. To win the bet all the teams selected must win their matches, if they don’t we lose. Some bookmakers offer a refund on your stake if one team lets you down on accumulators which have 5 teams or more, this can ease the pain of not winning your accumulator.\r\n<h2>What are the advantages of a win accumulator?</h2>\r\nThe main advantages of a win accumulator is you can turn a very small amount of money into a life changing amount in just 90 minutes. This is why accumulators are so popular, if you only have a £5 or £10 pot for the week  you can place a couple of £1 or £2 accumulators to return over £10,000 each. Accumulators are fun and good value for money, you can get unbelievable amounts of enjoyment watching the Football with just a £1 or £2 bet on. Below you can see a great example of turning a very small amount of money into a huge amount!\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.freesupertips.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/acca.png"><img class="size-full wp-image-4450" src="http://www.freesupertips.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/acca.png" alt="accumulator tips" width="396" height="579" /></a>\r\n<h2>How do I pick good win Football accumulator tips?</h2>\r\nWhen we are looking for our win accumulator tips we look at our Football betting statistics. These will show you teams form from the last six matches. Looking at the stats will help  you make a quick, easy decision on whether to add them to your accumulator. They cover a whole range of leagues, cups and competitions from all around the world so make sure you check them out before placing your bets.\r\n\r\nThere are multiple strategies that are good to use when looking for good accumulator tips. Our favourite is to look for teams who have good home form, teams always have an advantage playing at home and there can be some real value in close games picking the home side at good odds.\r\n\r\nAlternatively you can look for good teams playing away from home for better odds, for example Man City to beat Sunderland away from home would be decent odds to stick in your accumulator because more often than not they’ll win comfortably.\r\n\r\nThe third and final popular strategy is to back a draw accumulator. These can return huge amounts from as little as 3 or 4 games however they can be very hard to predict draws but if you manage to the pay out is worth it. £10 on three draws will roughly return 50/1 which is a very nice pay day.\r\n<h2>Where can I get a win accumulator free bet?</h2>\r\nOur <a href="http://www.freesupertips.co.uk/free-bets/">free bet section</a> has over £500’s worth of free bets and bonuses for you to back our accumulators risk free.  We told you earlier that accumulators are a great way to turn a small amount of money into a large amount so claim your free bets and bonuses now!\r\n<h2>Do you offer any other Football accumulator tips?</h2>\r\nWe offer a wide variety of football accumulator tips other than our win accumulator on a daily basis, check out the others below\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li style="text-align: left;"><span style="color: #000000;"><a style="color: #000000;" href="http://www.freesupertips.co.uk/both-teams-to-score-tips/">Both Teams To Score</a></span></li>\r\n 	<li style="text-align: left;"><span style="color: #000000;"><a style="color: #000000;" href="http://www.freesupertips.co.uk/both-teams-to-score-and-win-accumulator/">Both Teams To Score &amp; Win</a></span></li>\r\n 	<li style="text-align: left;"><span style="color: #000000;"><a style="color: #000000;" href="http://www.freesupertips.co.uk/premier-league-accumulator-betting-tips/">Premier League</a></span></li>\r\n 	<li style="text-align: left;"><span style="color: #000000;"><a style="color: #000000;" href="http://www.freesupertips.co.uk/uefa-champions-l