(705, 1, '2018-01-05 05:20:27', '2018-01-05 05:20:27', '<p>A both teams to score and win accumulator is a new and very popular type of bet. For us to win the bet we need both teams to score and the team we select to win. Therefore we need scores of 2-1, 3-1, 3-2, 4-2, 4-3, etc if we pick the home team to win and both teams to score. You don’t have to pick a team to win you can actually back both teams to score and draw which can usually be found under the same both teams to score and match result market.</p><h2>What is a goal rush accumulator?</h2><p>A goal rush accumulator is simply a both teams to score and win accumulator. This is the term used by some bookmakers on their weekend coupons so you can quickly identify what coupon it is. Ladbrokes are one of the bookmakers that do this, if you <strong><a title="ladbrokes" href="http://bit.ly/LadbrokesNew2">visit their site here</a> </strong>you can see they have a goal rush accumulator coupon listed for this weekends action.</p><h2>What are the advantages of a both teams to score and win accumulator?</h2><p><strong>Big odds</strong> is the main advantage of both teams to score and win accumulators, for a game like Arsenal to beat Spurs and both teams to score you’re looking at odds of 3/1 as a single. When you start to build your accumulator you’re looking at around 40/1 for three games, 130/1 for four games and so on.</p><p><strong>Huge profit</strong> is another advantage of the both teams to score and win accumulators,&nbsp;You can see from above that even from a four match accumulator you can return over £1,000 from just a £10 stake. By placing even a small amount on a 4-6 team both teams to score an win accumulator you can return a huge amount of money which is what we all want.</p><h2>How do I pick good both teams to score and win tips?</h2><p>I use a similar strategy to picking these bet as I use with my <a title="both teams to score accumulator tips" href="http://stagingonline.net/projects/freesupertips/both-teams-to-score-tips/">both teams accumulator tips</a>.</p><p>Good teams playing<strong> Away from home</strong>&nbsp;is a great strategy when looking for good both teams to score and win tips. If you look at teams like Barcelona and Real Madrid they are often short when playing away from home to win but you can get around 15/8 for them to win and concede. Teams who have good scoring records at home will often still find the net against the majority good teams. A few exceptions to this rule would be teams like Chelsea who have a very good defence and goal keeper. They also score a lot of goals early on in games which allows them to park the bus in the second half and play on the counter attack which results in them not conceding.</p><p>Another strategy is to look at teams with <strong>poor defenses and good attackers&nbsp;</strong>again Barcelona and Real Madrid are prime examples. You can make a lot of money backing these two sides away from home in singles or doubles. The gap in class in La Liga between the big two and the rest of the table is massive so they’ll often be 3-0 up and let their foot off the gas which often means conceding. I would avoid good teams with poor defences for this bet though, if you look at Man United’s defence they concede far too many goals away from home which results in poor form.</p><h2>Looking for more FREE Football tips?</h2><p>We hope you enjoy our free both teams to score and win accumulator tips, we also offer a wide variety of other Football tips which are of course all free. If you’re interested in finding more free tips then just click here to view our complete range of free Football tips.</p>', 'What is a both teams to score and win accumulator', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'what-is-a-both-teams-to-score-and-win-accumulator', '', '', '2018-01-16 09:14:33', '2018-01-16 09:14:33', '', 0, 'http://stagingonline.net/projects/freesupertips/?post_type=tips&#038;p=705', 0, 'tips', '', 0);
