cks from our previews to try and win a large amount from a small stake.</p><p><strong>Anytime Touchdown Scorers</strong></p><p>Another one of our popular NFL picks is our anytime touchdown scorer accumulator. A player is picked from a selection of games to score a touchdown anytime and put into an accumulator. This is another great chance to follow our NFL tips and win big from a small stake.</p><h2>Expert NFL Picks Against The Spread &amp; Totals</h2><p>It doesn’t matter what week of the season it is, our team of tipsters&nbsp;are here to assist you with&nbsp;their expert NFL betting tips. Our previews contain our NFL picks against the spread and totals for every single game of the week. Our tipsters also provide reasons as to why they’re backing each bet, giving you the option to follow our tipsters’ NFL predictions or use the reasoning to help with your own NFL betting research.</p><p>For those of you who are new&nbsp;and want to bet on the NFL, take a look at our explanations of two of the major markets we use for our NFL predictions:</p><p><strong>NFL Picks – Handicaps/Point Spreads</strong></p><p>Betting against the spread works like handicap betting in football. For example, our tipsters pick &nbsp;New England Patriots -2.5 point spread in this weeks’ NFL predictions. This means the Patriots must win the game by 3 or more points for us to win the bet.</p><p>If the pick was New England Patriots -3 point spread and they win by exactly 3 points (e.g. 23-20) then we receive a refund. If this happens in the leg of an accumulator our bet can still win at reduced odds&nbsp;as this leg becomes void.</p><p><strong>NFL Picks – Totals</strong></p><p>Total match points work similar to betting against the spread but instead of handicaps it’s total match points we’re interested in. For example, if our tipsters pick Over 57 total match points in New England Patriots vs Atlanta Falcons this week we need more than 57 points in the match to win this bet. However, if there is e