(842, 1, '2018-01-22 05:44:02', '2018-01-22 05:44:02', '<div class="text-content">\r\n\r\nSwansea had a brief respite from their Premier League misery in midweek as they beat Championship leaders Wolves in their FA Cup Replay to progress to the 4th round, although the fact they could well be replaced by Wolves in next season’s top flight will still be weighing heavily on their minds.\r\n\r\nIn fairness, Carlos Carvalhal has significantly improved The Swans’ since taking over as manager, and that 2-1 win against Wolves makes it three games without defeat in all competitions. Their previous two did end all square against the likes of Wolves and Newcastle though, so they won’t be aiming too high just yet.\r\n\r\nSwansea’s home form isn’t exactly promising either. They have won just two Premier League games at The Liberty Stadium this season, drawing twice and losing the remaining seven matches, a record which has contributed greatly to their bottom of the table standing. Now they face a Liverpool side coming off the back of a huge victory at Anfield last weekend.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<div class="fb-sb-head bg-betfair">\r\n<h4>200/1 Swansea vs Liverpool #OddsOnThat</h4>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="fb-sb-content">\r\n<div class="fb-sb-subhead">Over 2.5 Match Goals, Firmino and Mane to score, Olsson and Carroll to be carded.</div>\r\n<div class="fb-sb-button-wrapper">\r\n<div class="fb-sb-button">BET NOW</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nMohamed Salah absolutely ran the show against Manchester City as he continues to improve under Jurgen Klopp, with the hosts winning a thrilling 4-3 match and resigning Manchester City to their first defeat of the league season. It may have been nervy at the end as Manchester City pulled two goals back, but Liverpool fully deserved the victory and will be brimming with confidence.\r\n\r\nThis victory made it five on the bounce in all competitions, and they are unbeaten in a very impressive 18 competitive games. This takes them to 3rd in 