(854, 1, '2018-01-24 07:44:27', '2018-01-24 07:44:27', '<p>Follow our tips by adding them to your bet slip automatically. Enter your stake and place the bet to follow, simple! Use one of our <a href="/free-bets/">free bets</a> to follow risk free.</p>\r\n<ul class="tips-meta-links">\r\n                  <li><strong><a href="/how-to-follow-our-football-tips/">How to follow our Football Tips</a></strong></li>\r\n                  <li><strong><a href="/5819-profit-2015-2016-football-season/">Football Tips - £5,819 profit this season</a></strong></li>\r\n                  <li><strong><a href="https://twitter.com/#" target="_blank">Follow us on Twitter</a></strong></li>\r\n\r\n               </ul>\r\n<div itemscope="" itemtype="http://schema.org/Product" class="fst red segment tip-content"><div class="golf-image"></div><h1 itemprop="name" class="ui header" style="margin-top:0px;">Super Bowl Bets &amp; Super Bowl Predictions for 2018</h1><div itemprop="description" style="color:#333; padding:0 12px;"><p><strong>We take a look at six teams primed to make a run at the Lombardi trophy and discuss the best preseason Super Bowl 52 bets. We</strong><strong>&nbsp;can hardly wait for the new season to start… so let’s get to our Super Bowl 52 predictions.</strong></p><h2><strong><em>Preseason Super Bowl 52 Bets</em></strong></h2><p><strong>#6&nbsp;</strong><strong><u>Tennessee Titans</u></strong></p><p><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-19821" src="http://www.freesupertips.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/Corbis-42-78996561.jpg" alt="Tennessee Titans NFL" width="640" height="427" srcset="http://www.freesupertips.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/Corbis-42-78996561.jpg 640w, http://www.freesupertips.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/Corbis-42-78996561-360x240.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px"></p><p>Marcus Mariota is starting to look like an<strong> elite </strong>NFL quarterback. He and stud TE Delanie Walker have a proven chemistry. Add newly acquired WR Eric Decker into the mix. Plus they drafted stud WR Corey Davis. Mariota will have plenty of talented receivers to decimate defenses.</p><p>They’re bringing back beastly RB DeMarco Murray who rushed for nearly 1300 yards last season with 9 TD’s. Plus having a top rated offensive line always helps. I’m expecting them to do quite well and make a Super Bowl push.</p><p>They also drafted talented cornerback Adoree’ Jackson to sure up the backend. Defensive coordinator Dick LeBeau is a proven mastermind who will find ways to pressure teams and create turnovers.</p><p>And don’t forget that Tennessee is in a weak division —the AFC South. The Texans still don’t have a proven quarterback and the Colts o-line was terribly shaky last year. The Titans should get into the post season. And if they do —anything could happen.</p><h3>50/1 – Tennessee Titans to win Super Bowl 52!</h3><p><strong>#5&nbsp;</strong><strong><u>Dallas Cowboys</u></strong></p><p>Dallas would be higher on the list, but with Ezekiel Elliot suspended for the first 6 games —pending an appeal — The ‘Boys shave slipped into the #5 spot. Zeke is a key cog to their offense.</p><p>But keep in mind that QB Dak Prescott had a phenomenal season last year —and they have Dez Bryant, Jason Witten, and newly drafted WR Ryan Switzer. Plus developmental TE Rico Geathers looks like a beast. Snag him in the late rounds of fantasy football if you’re smart.</p><p>But even with perhaps the #1 offensive line in football, Zeke is a big loss. McFadden is mediocre at best. Dallas will face the Giants, The Cardinals, the Packers, and the Broncos without Zeke. Luckily they have a week 6 bye. If they start the season 1-4 or 2-3 it will hurt their chances.</p><p>Plus, they have plenty of players on defense facing suspensions. On the bright side, top draft pick Jaylon Smith is looking good. And they drafted two very talented rookie cornerbacks. I think when the smoke clears the Cowboys will make a strong push the second half of the season and have a pretty good chance of going to Super Bowl 52.</p><a class="fb-sb-wrapper in-content bg-offset-paddy-power ppc-paddy-power advert_event" title="14/1 Dallas Cowboys to win Super Bowl 52!" target="_blank" href="http://bit.ly/2xAebly"><div class="fb-sb-head bg-paddy-power"><h4>14/1 Dallas Cowboys to win Super Bowl 52!</h4></div><div class="fb-sb-content"><div class="fb-sb-subhead">£20 risk free bet for new Paddy Power customers<br><span>New customers only. T&amp;Cs apply, 18+, begambleaware.org</span></div><div class="fb-sb-button-wrapper"><div class="fb-sb-button">BET NOW</div></div></div> </a><p><strong>#4 </strong><strong><u>Green Bay Packers</u></strong></p><p>Last year the Packers seemed cursed. They lost many offensive and defensive stars due to injury. And they <em>still </em>made it to the NFC championship match vs Atlanta. They’ll start the year healthy and should make a nice push for the Super Bowl.</p><p>They’ll have to duke it out with the Cowboys. But any time Aaron Rodgers is your quarterback, you have a legitimate shot at going to the big game. With top draft picks Kevin King and Josh Jones, their backend will have more depth, should injuries arise.</p><p>Green Bay has a tough schedule —playing the Falcons, Seahawks and Cowboys within the first 5 weeks. But once they get over the hump things should get easier.</p><p>They tend to come on strong towards the end of the season —when it counts. If they can keep their star studded WR receiving corps healthy —Jordy Nelson, Cobb, and Adams —they are always a threat. Now add newly acquired TE Martellus Bennett to the mix and they’re even more dangerous.</p><h3>10/1 – Green Bay Packers to win Super Bowl 52!</h3><p><strong>#3 </strong><strong><u>New England Patriots </u></strong></p><p>Last year’s defending Super Bowl champs are a favorite to win it all again. As long as Tom Brady and Belichick are together, they’ll be legitimate contenders.</p><p>They’ll have Gronk, Amendola, and Chris Hogan returning. Plus 